  "texts": [
    "From the 25,217 notes from the 795 patients, the four automated methods flagged a total of 1,411 notes (Supplementary Table S3).",
    "Given how the models were designed, JSL was only able to flag notes related to housing in general (housing noted), while Regex could not distinguish between current and past housing instability.",
    "Both GPT-4 and GPT-3.5 were able to flag notes related to general housing status, housing instability current, and housing instability past.",
    "After the models were run on the 25,217 notes, we selected notes that were flagged as housing noted for JSL, housing instability current or past for Regex, and housing instability current or housing instability past for GPT-4 and GPT-3.5.",
    "The most commonly flagged note types were assessments, plan of care, OB Triage, History and Physical (H&P), consults, discharge summary, and ED (emergency department) notes, indicating that these types of notes are most likely to provide relevant information related to housing and/or housing instability (Supplementary Table S4)."
